---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Course" description="LLMs for Social Science — courses at Oxford, Sciences Po Paris, and the European University Institute.">
  <div class="container container--content">

    <div class="page-header">
      <p class="section-label">Course</p>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">LLMs for Social Science</h1>
      <p class="page-header__desc">
        An intensive course on using language models in social science research.
        Delivered at Oxford, Sciences Po Paris, and the European University Institute.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>2026 Dates & Locations</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-3 mt-4 mb-8">
      <div class="card card--accent-top">
        <span class="tag">Upcoming</span>
        <h3 class="card__title" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">Oxford</h3>
        <p class="card__text">
          March 23–27, 2026<br />
          5-day intensive. DPIR, University of Oxford.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card__title">Sciences Po Paris</h3>
        <p class="card__text">
          April 7, 2026<br />
          1-day workshop.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card__title">EUI Florence</h3>
        <p class="card__text">
          April 20–21, 2026<br />
          2-day workshop. European University Institute.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Syllabus Overview</h2>
      <p>
        The course covers the full pipeline of working with LLMs as a social scientist:
        from understanding transformer architectures and tokenization to fine-tuning,
        evaluation, and deployment. Emphasis on practical coding exercises and
        research applications.
      </p>
      <p>
        <!-- Detailed syllabus to be added -->
        <em>Detailed 2026 syllabus coming soon.</em>
      </p>

      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <p>
        Participants should have basic familiarity with Python and statistics.
        No prior experience with deep learning or NLP is required — the course
        builds up from fundamentals. For those who want to prepare, see the
        <a href="/resources/">resources page</a> for preliminary materials.
      </p>

      <h2>Materials</h2>
      <p>
        All course materials are open-source and available on the
        <a href="https://github.com/Oxford-LLMs-Research/llms-social-science-course" target="_blank" rel="noopener">course GitHub repository</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
